00:17:56.280 --> 00:17:57.694
fit into your business?

00:17:57.694 --> 00:18:00.110
Can you tell me anything else,
like assets and management?

00:18:00.110 --> 00:18:03.330
JOSH BROWN: So we are
the strangest version

00:18:03.330 --> 00:18:04.890
of our type of work.

00:18:04.890 --> 00:18:07.420
Our friends call it Registered
Investment Advisory.

00:18:07.420 --> 00:18:09.180
Everyone's heard the term RIA.

00:18:09.180 --> 00:18:10.740
Basically, we're non-brokerage.

00:18:10.740 --> 00:18:13.020
Were fiduciary only.

00:18:13.020 --> 00:18:18.520
Managing money for high networth
households and small pensions,

00:18:18.520 --> 00:18:19.470
endowments.

00:18:19.470 --> 00:18:25.040
And we're very strange in
that most RIAs in the country,

00:18:25.040 --> 00:18:27.130
they look more like barbershops.

00:18:27.130 --> 00:18:29.110
It's usually a
sole practitioner,

00:18:29.110 --> 00:18:31.060
maybe has a few
people-- or she has

00:18:31.060 --> 00:18:35.380
a few people working for him
or her, but they're local.

00:18:35.380 --> 00:18:38.500
So they're in the office
complex that's on Main Street,

00:18:38.500 --> 00:18:40.930
or they might even
have a storefront.

00:18:40.930 --> 00:18:43.300
And all the customers come
because they play golf

00:18:43.300 --> 00:18:45.550
at the country club where
all the other wealthy people

00:18:45.550 --> 00:18:49.930
in town play, and it's very
familial and, you could say,

00:18:49.930 --> 00:18:51.640
incestuous.

00:18:51.640 --> 00:18:57.220
And these are relationships that
are based on personality stuff

00:18:57.220 --> 00:18:58.309
and geography.

00:18:58.309 --> 00:19:00.100
They're not really
based on-- this person's

00:19:00.100 --> 00:19:02.260
a really good investor.

00:19:02.260 --> 00:19:03.940
I think we've broken that mold.

00:19:03.940 --> 00:19:06.640
Most of our clients are
nowhere near where we're based.

00:19:06.640 --> 00:19:08.560
We're based in New York.

00:19:08.560 --> 00:19:11.920
I think our biggest client
base is on the west coast--

00:19:11.920 --> 00:19:16.960
up from Portland, all the
way down to San Diego.

00:19:16.960 --> 00:19:19.270
And then we've got big
pockets of clientele

00:19:19.270 --> 00:19:21.370
in places like
Austin and Chicago.

00:19:21.370 --> 00:19:23.920
And a lot of clients
we've not met,

00:19:23.920 --> 00:19:26.380
or we meet them six months
into the relationship.

00:19:26.380 --> 00:19:27.940
We're already
managing their money.

00:19:27.940 --> 00:19:30.370
They tend to be
more progressive--

00:19:30.370 --> 00:19:33.400
a lot of people that
work in technology.

00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:35.290
And what they all
have in common is

00:19:35.290 --> 00:19:39.520
that they're not hung up on
having a local office in town.

00:19:39.520 --> 00:19:42.670
They just want the best
people that there are.

00:19:42.670 --> 00:19:45.280
And if that's a telephone or
a relationship on the web,

00:19:45.280 --> 00:19:46.330
they're OK with that.

00:19:46.330 --> 00:19:50.200
We bridge the gap
by doing content--

00:19:50.200 --> 00:19:52.720
so Twitter, blogs.

00:19:52.720 --> 00:19:56.320
We have 5 of the top 20
independent financial advisor

00:19:56.320 --> 00:19:58.180
blogs in the country.

00:19:58.180 --> 00:20:00.910
24/7 we're putting
out our thoughts

00:20:00.910 --> 00:20:07.060
on markets, economics, the nexus
of politics with investing.

00:20:07.060 --> 00:20:09.280
And our clients know
where they can find what

00:20:09.280 --> 00:20:11.510
our thoughts are at all times.

00:20:11.510 --> 00:20:14.870
So we've built fans, and
fans have become clients,

00:20:14.870 --> 00:20:18.400
and that is the best way to
build a business, I think,

00:20:18.400 --> 00:20:21.110
in the 21st century.

00:20:21.110 --> 00:20:24.150
And I think as people
here are aware of--

00:20:24.150 --> 00:20:27.340
and maybe in finance, it's
dawning on the industry--

00:20:27.340 --> 00:20:29.980
the scarce resource
is not capital.

00:20:29.980 --> 00:20:31.710
You just showed me a slide.

00:20:31.710 --> 00:20:35.080
There's more capital out in
the world than ever before.

00:20:35.080 --> 00:20:37.160
The scarce resource
is attention.

00:20:37.160 --> 00:20:39.080
How do you get attention?

00:20:39.080 --> 00:20:44.000
Well, I'm not pretty enough
to get a lot on Instagram.

00:20:44.000 --> 00:20:46.660
But on the web and
on Twitter, you

00:20:46.660 --> 00:20:48.910
can get attention
by being helpful

00:20:48.910 --> 00:20:50.770
and by saying things
that are true.

00:20:50.770 --> 00:20:53.260
Maybe even things
that are uncomfortable

00:20:53.260 --> 00:20:55.930
but that have to be confronted.

00:20:55.930 --> 00:20:58.030
When you do a daily
investment blog

00:20:58.030 --> 00:21:00.100
and you're giving people
the data that they

00:21:00.100 --> 00:21:01.810
need to make smart
decisions, rather than

00:21:01.810 --> 00:21:05.530
emotional decisions, you can
get a lot of positive attention

00:21:05.530 --> 00:21:09.400
for putting that stuff out
there, not charging for it,

00:21:09.400 --> 00:21:12.400
not keeping it
gated, and not acting

00:21:12.400 --> 00:21:14.290
like you invented the truth.

00:21:14.290 --> 00:21:16.190
You're just presenting people--

00:21:16.190 --> 00:21:16.940
here's the data.

00:21:16.940 --> 00:21:19.690
Here's the evidence for why
these types of investors

00:21:19.690 --> 00:21:23.120
do better than those
types of investors.

00:21:23.120 --> 00:21:26.500
So if it's an attention economy
and you're out there earning

00:21:26.500 --> 00:21:30.130
the right type of attention,
you can build an amazing brand,

00:21:30.130 --> 00:21:31.780
and you can build
a fan base that

00:21:31.780 --> 00:21:34.110
become clients of your service.

00:21:34.110 --> 00:21:37.130
And we started the firm
less than five years ago.

00:21:37.130 --> 00:21:40.900
We were just under $90 million,
four people managing it.

00:21:40.900 --> 00:21:44.030
We're 24 people less
than five years later.

00:21:44.030 --> 00:21:46.570
We just broke $800
million under management,

00:21:46.570 --> 00:21:48.670
and we've opened
offices in Chicago,

00:21:48.670 --> 00:21:52.810
in Newport Beach, California,
Portland, Long Island, Florida.

00:21:52.810 --> 00:21:55.420
And we're talking to advisors
all over the country that

00:21:55.420 --> 00:21:59.740
want to be part of this movement
of evidence-based investing,

00:21:59.740 --> 00:22:01.330
putting the customer first.

00:22:01.330 --> 00:22:04.210
And all of this is happening
as a result of digital.

00:22:04.210 --> 00:22:06.430
We don't take out newspaper ads.

00:22:06.430 --> 00:22:09.720
All of this is because
of social media.

