just to give you a
little bit of background,

00:31:48.430 --> 00:31:50.440
and then I'll answer your
question specifically.

00:31:50.440 --> 00:31:53.290
Our investment beliefs
are that less is more.

00:31:53.290 --> 00:31:56.350
There are simple
answers to complexities.

00:31:56.350 --> 00:32:00.310
Not every complexity needs to
be met with more complexity.

00:32:00.310 --> 00:32:02.080
Cost matters.

00:32:02.080 --> 00:32:05.710
After tax returns matter
a lot more than what

00:32:05.710 --> 00:32:07.660
particular investment you buy.

00:32:07.660 --> 00:32:10.090
So we've got this
overarching philosophy of--

00:32:10.090 --> 00:32:13.270
let's not go in there and
twiddle the knobs every day.

00:32:13.270 --> 00:32:15.670
Let's let markets
do what they do,

00:32:15.670 --> 00:32:18.580
and let's build durable,
rules-based portfolios

00:32:18.580 --> 00:32:20.241
where the rules
are set in advance

00:32:20.241 --> 00:32:22.240
and we're not using our
gut instincts for things

00:32:22.240 --> 00:32:24.280
like market timing.

00:32:24.280 --> 00:32:27.100
Now, that works for, let's say,
