00:49:31.870 --> 00:49:34.740
because if people say
something on their air

00:49:34.740 --> 00:49:38.710
and it moves the price of
an investment instrument,

00:49:38.710 --> 00:49:42.220
they want that thing that
was said to have been true.

00:49:42.220 --> 00:49:43.930
And then each
individual person that

00:49:43.930 --> 00:49:47.170
comes on the air, if they're
an investor and not just a TV

00:49:47.170 --> 00:49:50.680
personality, has their
own compliance regulations

00:49:50.680 --> 00:49:53.650
to contend with.

00:49:53.650 --> 00:49:56.480
So I can't speak
for everyone else,

00:49:56.480 --> 00:50:04.630
but I can tell you that I have
to disclose all of my holdings.

00:50:04.630 --> 00:50:08.800
And during the show they pop
it up, Josh owns these things.

00:50:08.800 --> 00:50:11.680
What they don't want people
to do is say one thing

00:50:11.680 --> 00:50:13.180
but do the other thing.

00:50:13.180 --> 00:50:16.990
So they don't want people to
come on and say, I love Target,

00:50:16.990 --> 00:50:20.680
and then be shorting the
stock after it pops up,

00:50:20.680 --> 00:50:21.740
for obvious reasons.

00:50:21.740 --> 00:50:24.220
And I don't think there's
a lot of that going on.

00:50:24.220 --> 00:50:27.400
It would be so counter
to your interests

00:50:27.400 --> 00:50:29.920
if you were doing media
on a regular basis

00:50:29.920 --> 00:50:33.520
to pull off one trade and try to
